<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Albanians Urge Inclusion of Province in Summit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Albanians Urge Inclusion of Province in Summit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2204205094 Tirana TVSH Television Network in Albanian 1800 
GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2204205094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana TVSH Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Albanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A communique by the government of republic of 
Kosova states that an international summit on Bosnia, proposed 
by Russian President Yeltsin and agreed upon by U.S. President 
Clinton, must include the Kosova question. The communique 
further states that peace can never be achieved in the Balkans 
as long as the Serbian repression against 2 million Albanians of 
Kosova is not stopped and the independence of the republic of 
Kosova is not ensured. The government of the republic of Kosova 
asks the United Nations, the United States, the European Union, 
and Russia to earnestly include the question of Kosova in the 
peace process. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

