<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bukoshi Issues Similar Proposal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bukoshi Issues Similar Proposal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2204193394 Pristina KOSOVA DAILY REPORT Nr. 341 in English 
22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2204193394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pristina KOSOVA DAILY REPORT Nr. 341 </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Bukoshi: Future Peace Talks on </F>
Balkans Should Include Kosova" -- issued by the Democratic 
League of Kosova] 
  [Text] In a statement issued yesterday, prime minister of 
the republic of Kosova Dr. Bujar Bukoshi said that an 
international summit on Bosnia, proposed Tuesday by Russian 
President Boris Yeltsin and endorsed by President Clinton should 
be broadened to also include the Kosova question. "Peace will 
never come to the Balkans until the repression by Serbia of 2 
Million Albanians in Kosova is lifted and independence is 
granted to the republic of Kosova. The Kosova issue must be in 
the agenda of any international conference on the Balkans." Dr. 
Bukoshi called on the United Nations, the U.S., the European 
Union to fully include Kosova in the peace process. "No true 
peace can occur in the Balkans until there is an end to the 
brutal Serbian repression which continues unabated in our 
republic," the statement says. 

</TEXT>

