<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Situation in Gorazde -- 25 April </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Situation in Gorazde -- 25 April </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    More U.N. Troops Arrive </H4>

<F P=102> LD2504105194 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1030 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2504105194 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" item] </F>
  [Text] Belgrade, April 25 (TANJUG) -- Another 247 members 
of the U.N. Protection Force (UNPROFOR) were early on Monday [25 
April] deployed between the warring local Serb and Muslim troops 
in Gorazde, Muslim enclave in southeast Bosnia-Herzegovina, a 
U.N. spokesman said. According to REUTERS, the British, Russian 
and Egyptian soldiers joined the 200 U.N. troops which had 
arrived in Gorazde on Saturday. The aim of the U.N. 
peacekeepers in Gorazde is to form a buffer between the 
belligerent sides, to secure the safety of the humanitarian 
agencies and monitor the withdrawal of the Serb heavy artillery 
to 20 km away from the centre of the town, as called by a NATO 
ultimatum which expires at midnight Tuesday. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

