<H3> <TI>   French General: Serbs Complying </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    French General: Serbs Complying </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2404172894 Paris AFP in English 1627 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2404172894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Zagreb, April 24 (AFP) -- Bosnian Serb forces 
appear to have complied with a NATO ultimatum to withdraw three 
kilometers from the center of Gorazde or face air strikes, the 
head of UN forces in the former Yugoslavia said Sunday [24 
April]. In an interview with AFP here, French General Bertrand 
de Lapresle said the Serbs were observing a ceasefire and "have 
withdrawn beyond the three-kilometer line, as far as we can 
tell." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

