<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbian Expellees Return </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbian Expellees Return </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2404170794 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1643 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2404170794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cajnice, 24 Apr (TANJUG) -- The return of Serbs 
expelled from their homes by the Muslims began this afternoon at 
the same time as the deployment of UN Protection Forces 
[UNPROFOR] troops along the demarcation line between the warring 
sides on the Gorazde front. Several hundred Serbian civilians 
from Donja Potkozara, Gornja Potkozara, Zupcici, Lug, Visevica, 
and other villages have returned to their homes after almost two 
years spent as refugees. They decided to return after UN 
representatives offered them guarantees that they would be 
secure. On their return the Serbian civilians found utter 
devastation in their villages because the Muslims had razed and 
burned to the ground all houses and other buildings. However, 
they hope that they will receive aid in rebuilding their razed 
homes and that UNPROFOR representatives will be a true guarantee 
that the Muslims will not massacre them in their villages again. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-9310 </DOCNO>
