<H3> <TI>   Situation in Gorazde -- 23 April </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Situation in Gorazde -- 23 April </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Attack Diminishing </H4>

<F P=102> LD2304204694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 2000 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2304204694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Fahrudin Becic from Gorazde] </F>
  [Text] Overflights by NATO planes were again registered 
sometime before 2200 hours. The activities of the aggressor 
have significantly diminished compared to this afternoon and the 
early hours of this evening, but tank and howitzer shells are 
from time to time landing on the town. Firing from infantry 
weapons has also diminished in intensity compared to what it was 
an hour or so ago. However, there are no indications that the 
aggressor is withdrawing, something that is demanded by the NATO 
ultimatum. But there is evidence that attacks on the Rogatica 
and Pale areas of the battlefield are intensifying. Fresh and 
stormy events are probably in store in this area. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-9313 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu079_i_94011" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-079 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  23 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Situation in Gorazde -- 23 April </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Situation in Gorazde -- 23 April </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Attack Kills 21 </H4>

<F P=102> LD2304204894 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 2000 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2304204894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Fahrudin Becic for Bosnia-Herzegovina Radio and </F>
Television] 
  [Text] After a very short break between 1800 and 1900, 
explosions can be heard again in Gorazde. Several apartment 
blocks have been hit by tank shells. Buildings in the immediate 
vicinity of UNPROFOR [UN Protection Force] were also hit. 
Several shells completely destroyed three apartments. Again, 
there are killed and injured. From 0800 up to this moment, 
according to incomplete statistics, 21 people have been killed 
in Gorazde and 53 wounded. 
  At about 2100 chetnik forces began using anti-aircraft guns 
and infantry weapons to fire on housing in the town center and 
buildings around the hospital. The consequences of these 
activities are not yet known, while at this moment, at about 
2117, howitzer shells are landing on the town. Chetniks today 
launched fierce attacks from the direction of Pale. Four tanks, 
several armored vehicles, and strong infantry forces took part 
in these attacks. Actions from the direction of Rogatica and 
along the demarcation line northwest of the town were 
intensifying. There is no precise information on the events in 
this area. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

