<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NATO Extends Ultimatum To Other Safe Areas </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2304025294 Belgrade TANJUG in English 0019 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2304025294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" item] </F>
  [Text] Brussels, April 22 (TANJUG) -- The North Atlantic 
Council late on Friday night [22 April] extended its ultimatum 
to Bosnian Serbs to cmver the other U.N.-designated `safe 
havens' in Bosnia-Herzegovina. A statement released from the 
session said that Bosnian Serb armament would be targeted if 
they attacked the `safe havens' of Gorazde, Bihac, Srebrenica, 
Tuzla and Zepa from heavy weapons or in other ways. The towns 
were designated `safe havens' in spring of 1993. 

</TEXT>

