<H3> <TI>   Bosnian Serb Vice President Calls For Summit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bosnian Serb Vice President Calls For Summit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2404105994 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1011 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2404105994 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Jagodina, 24 Apr (TANJUG) -- Biljana Plavsic, vice 
president of the republic of Srpska, said today that by 
withdrawing its forces from around Gorazde the republic of 
Srpska showed the world that it is in favor of the peaceful 
resolution of the crisis, even though its army did not carry out 
any aggression there but was on the defensive. In a Jagodina 
Radio program called "Weekend" she noted that "some people 
regret not having seen bombardment last night, which forebodes 
fresh provocations" and added that for this reason a summit 
between Russia, America, the European Union, and the United 
Nations should be held as soon as possible, in order to clarify 
the issues completely and restore a permanent peace. 

</TEXT>

