<H3> <TI>   TANJUG: Muslims Order Downing of NATO Planes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    TANJUG: Muslims Order Downing of NATO Planes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2404120294 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1143 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2404120294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Banja Luka, April 24 (TANJUG) -- The command of the 
7th Corps of the Moslem force ordered its units which are in 
close contact with forces of the Serb Republic army to open fire 
on all NATO planes which fly over the line of separation, TANJUG 
learned from well informed Bosnian Serb military sources. The 
sources said that the 7th Corps of the Moslem force, in charge 
of central Bosnia-Herzegovina, had issued this order so that the 
blame for the possible downing of NATO planes, with a strong 
media campaign, could be pinned on the Bosnian Serb army and 
their ground positions punished. This would not be the first 
time that Moslem forces down NATO aircraft. In June last year, 
Moslems downed an Italian transport plane, the sources said, 
adding that world media had given little coverage to the 
incident although it had been proved, so that the Moslem 
leadership still relied on this support. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

