<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, April 22 (AFP) -- Bosnian Serb forces 
trapped a UN convoy Friday [22 April] when it began retreating 
to Sarajevo after failing to reach the besieged Moslem enclave 
of Gorazde, UNPROFOR spokesman Richard Pernod told AFP. The 
convoy, made up of some 100 French, British and Ukrainian 
peacekeepers from the UN Protection Force [UNPROFOR], was on its 
way to relieve Gorazde when it received orders to head back to 
Sarajevo but Serb forces stepped in and have stopped its 
retreat, he said. 

</TEXT>

