<H3> <TI>   Inter-Muslim Clashes Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Inter-Muslim Clashes Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2304225794 Belgrade TANJUG in English 2213 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2304225794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" item] </F>
  [Text] Doboj, April 23 (TANJUG) -- Moslem forces mounted 
strong attacks on Serbs in the broader area of Doboj in northern 
Bosnia, while inter-Moslem fighting continued in western Bosnia. 
As reported by military sources of Serbs in Bosnia, the Moslem 
forces were most active on the front near Teslic, southwest of 
Doboj, where, coupled with strong artillery support, they 
executed two strong attacks which were repelled. The town of 
Teslic, too, itself came under mortar fire. 
  There was fighting also northeast of Doboj, where the Moslem 
forces used all weapons at their disposal in the attacks on Serb 
positions. The Serb side was forced to respond, after which the 
attacks ceased. 
  Inter-Moslem fighting in western Bosnia, as reported by the 
Moslem-controlled Sarajevo Radio, continued along all the 
separation lines in the Cazin and Velika Kladusa municipalities. 
There was heavy fighting with the use of artillery and infantry 
since the early morning hours between the forces loyal to Moslem 
radical leader Alija Izetbegovic and the formations of the 
autonomous province of western Bosnia, which was last year 
formed the followers of peaceful solution to the crisis in 
Bosnia. 

</TEXT>

