<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbian Shelling Kills Five in Travnik Area </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbian Shelling Kills Five in Travnik Area </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2404180994 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2404180994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] There was no peace in the Travnik municipality 
today. The Serb-chetnik aggressors are firing shells of the 
largest caliber at civilian targets in the town and its suburbs. 
The aggressors also shelled defense lines in the Turbe area and 
launched combined infantry and artillery attacks on the Vlasic 
plateau. Five civilians were killed and a number wounded by 
howitzer and tank fire from enemy strongholds. As we file this 
report at 1850 the combined artillery and infantry attacks are 
still going on at 1850. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

