<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs: Muslims Trying To Capture Sarajevo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs: Muslims Trying To Capture Sarajevo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2204139994 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 2049 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2204139994 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Zvornik-Bratunac, 22 Apr (TANJUG) -- This morning 
Muslims launched artillery and infantry attacks on Serbian 
territory and defense lines of the Bosnian Serb republic army, 
whose final aim is to capture the Serbian part of Sarajevo. The 
attacks have not stopped this evening, TANJUG's correspondent 
has learned from Serbian military circles. 
  It is specified that, after several days of preparations and 
constant attacks, Moslem units launched attacks from the area of 
Olovo, Cemerka and Mountain Zvezda [all north of Sarajevo], and 
from the Breza and Visoko areas [northwest of Sarajevo]. They 
are using all available weapons. 
  The main targets of the Moslem offensive activity are 
Serbian 
villages and defense positions of the republic of Srpska army in 
the area of Ilijas [northwest of Sarajevo, toward Visoko], 
Srednje and in the Nisici plateau [both north of Sarajevo]. The 
attacks were accompanied by strong artillery support and mortar 
fire. 
  Republic of Srpska army units are responding to all attacks 
and successfully thwarting Moslem attempts at an infantry 
breakthrough of Serbian defense lines. Circles in the republic 
of Srpska army point out that the Moslems' intention is to cut 
the Ilijas-Srednje-Nisici communication link and take control of 
the Nisici plateau. They would then direct their actions toward 
Sarajevo, aiming at severing Serbian territory and occupying the 
Serbian part of Sarajevo. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

