<H3> <TI>   Major Tells Izetbegovic of Horror Over Gorazde </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Major Tells Izetbegovic of Horror Over Gorazde </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2304230494 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2304230494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] British Prime Minister John Major has sent a letter 
to Alija Izetbegovic, president of the Presidency of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, in which, among other things, he refers to 
the current aggression against Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  I am horrified by the brutality of the Bosnian Serb 
offensive 
on Gorazde. The basic task now must be a cease-fire not only in 
Gorazde, but throughout Bosnia. To this end Great Britain is 
actively taking part in the discussions in NATO and in all 
organizations in which a solution to this is being sought. A 
cease-fire by itself is not sufficient. A cease-fire must be 
followed by an agreement on a final solution that will require 
important territorial concessions by the Bosnian Serbs. The 
tragic events of the past few days stress the urgent need for 
the renewal of the peace process, the letter from Britain's 
Prime Minister John Major to President Izetbegovic says. 

</TEXT>

