<H3> <TI>   Russian Duma Delegation in Pale for Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Duma Delegation in Pale for Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2304120094 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1108 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2304120094 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, 23 Apr (TANJUG) -- A nine-member 
delegation of the Russian State Duma, led by Nikolay Bezbirodov, 
deputy chairman of the Commiteee for Defense and Security, 
arrived in Pale today and began talks with Vladimir Lukic, prime 
minister of the republic of Srpska. The two sides are 
discussing the present political and security situation in the 
wake of last night's NATO ultimatum to Serbs in the republic of 
Srpska and the agreement which Slobodan Milosevic, president of 
the Republic of Serbia, and Radovan Karadzic, president of the 
republic of Srpska, reached with Yasushi Akashi, the UN 
secretary general's special envoy, in Belgrade last night. The 
Russian parliamentarians arrived in Pale with specific proposals 
involving various aspects of economic and cultural cooperation 
between the Russian Federation and the republic of Srpska. 

