<H3> <TI>   Ganic in Zagreb for Consultations on Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ganic in Zagreb for Consultations on Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2204195794 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2204195794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Nada al-Isa from Zagreb] </F>
  [Text] Returning from Washington via Brussels, 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Presidency member Ejup Ganic today stopped in 
Zagreb. He used this stopover in Zagreb for political talks with 
the representatives of the Croatian leadership. He first held 
talks with Croatian Foreign Minister and deputy Prime Minister 
Mate Granic, while tonight he is due to meet with Croatian 
President Franjo Tudjman. The topic will be an exchange of 
opinions on the latest political situation after the tragedy in 
Gorazde, and the decisions of the U.S. Administration for wider 
involvement in Bosnia-Herzegovina. The Washington Agreement was 
also discussed, particularly ways of implementing it and in 
connection to this, future measures of the international 
community aimed at reaching lasting peace in Bosnia-Herzegovina 
and Croatia. This has been Nada al-Isa reporting from Zagreb for 
Radio Television Bosnia-Herzegovina. 

</TEXT>

