<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Berov Released From Hospital </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister Berov Released From Hospital </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2204093794 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 0900 
GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2204093794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Colonel Dr. Milan Petrov, chief of the Military 
Medical Academy, informed us a few minutes ago that this morning 
Prime Minister Lyuben Berov was released from the Lozenets 
Hospital. 
  It is up to the prime minister whether he will make use of 
the 15-20 day home rest, which is customary after a 
cardiovascular operation, or whether he will return immediately 
to regular activity, of which, according to the medical team, he 
is sufficiently able, Col. Dr. Milan Petrov said. 

</TEXT>

