<H3> <TI>   Daskalov, Slovakia's Kukan Discuss Trade </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Daskalov, Slovakia's Kukan Discuss Trade </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2204111794 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 0800 
GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2204111794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bilateral relations and common issues related to 
our integration in the European structures were discussed at the 
22 April meeting between Bulgarian Foreign Minister Stanislav 
Daskalov and Eduard Kukan, foreign minister of the Slovak 
Republic. 
  I was surprised to learn that the trade exchange between 
Bulgaria and Slovakia is shamefully small, and we agreed to 
encourage contacts between businessmen from the two countries, 
our foreign minister said. He said that it is necessary to 
review the contractual-legal basis between Bulgaria and Slovakia 
and sign a trade agreement in May. 

</TEXT>

