<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Situation in Gorazde -- 25 April </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Situation in Gorazde -- 25 April </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Serbs: Withdrawal Continues </H4>

<F P=102> LD2504103194 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1005 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2504103194 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Cajnice, 25 Apr (TANJUG) -- The cease-fire on 
the Gorazde front is today being violated only by Muslim snipers 
firing from the town center in a vain attempt to provoke the 
Serbian army, it has been announced in the command of the 
Herzegovina Corps [of the Bosnian Serb forces]. The command 
says that, in line with the Karadzic-Akashi agreement, the 
Serbian forces are today continuing to withdraw to 3 km from the 
center of Gorazde, while heavy weapons have been withdrawn to 
the agreed distance of 20 km. [passage omitted] Serbian 
military sources say that scattered Muslim forces are 
withdrawing from the center of Gorazde and regrouping in 
Orahovica, northwest of the town, probably planning to link up 
with their forces on Mount Igman near Sarajevo. 

</TEXT>

