of the Romanian Intelligence Service [SRI], Academician Yevgeniy 
Primakov, director of Russia's Foreign Intelligence Service, 
arrived in Bucharest. On this occasion, the two sides exchanged 
views on fighting international terrorism and organized crime as 
well as ways and means to stabilize the situation in various 
crisis spots. 
  Mr. Primakov was also received by Mr. Oliviu Gherman, 
president of the Senate, and by Prime Minister Nicolae Vacaroiu. 
He also had a talk with Mr. Vasile Vacaru, chairman of the 
joint standing commission of the two Parliament chambers for the 
exercise of parliamentary control over SRI activities -- a 
communique of the SRI Press Bureau reads. 

