<H3> <TI>   Army Refutes Allegations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Refutes Allegations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2604095494 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1900 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2604095494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>
<F P=105>  Romanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Press Bureau of the Romanian Army has faxed us 
a communique in which the Army comments on certain information 
that appeared in the press regarding allegations that trains 
with military signs carrying Russian tanks and troops have 
transited Romania. The Press Office of the Armed Forces 
mentions that the information issued by the A.M. Press, quoting 
National Railway Company information, does not correspond to 
reality. Romania was not asked and consequently did not agree 
to the transit of military trains belonging to the Russian 
Federation across its territory, the Press Bureau of the Army 
states. 

</TEXT>

