<F P=106> [Report by Mustafa Kurtovic] </F>
  [Text] Gorazde -- According to the information we received 
this morning from the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army East Bosnian 
Operative Group command in Gorazde, the chetniks have not 
withdrawn to a distance of 1 km from the town center as 
stipulated by the NATO ultimatum. Moreover, UN forces have not 
taken up the positions specified by the ultimatum. Groups of 
chetniks were sighted yesterday and this morning in areas that 
are only 1 km away from the town. Chetnik provocations 
overnight were registered in the area of Orahovice and 
(?Ostanica), while a tank and infantry attack at Brdarici is 
currently in progress. 
  Life in the city is extremely hard because the small area of 
the town now holds over 40,000 citizens and refugees who were 
forced to leave their homes in the surrounding villages. Lack 
of water could cause large-scale epidemics. That is why we are 
appealing to the UN Protection Force and health organizations to 
undertake urgent measures to protect the population of Gorazde 
from infectious diseases. As we were filing this report, we 
were informed that a UN High Commissioner for Refugees convoy, 
carrying food and medicine, had entered the town. 

