<H3> <TI>   French Crews Ordered To Refuse ID Checks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    French Crews Ordered To Refuse ID Checks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2504194694 Paris AFP in English 1936 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2504194694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Paris, April 25 (AFP) -- The French Government on 
Monday [25 April] ordered its helicopter crews involved in the 
evacuation of wounded people from Gorazde to refuse to submit to 
Bosnian Serb identity controls, the Foreign Ministry said. The 
restrictions on helicopter flights put in place by the Serbs are 
unacceptable, a Foreign Ministry spokeswoman, Catherine Colonna, 
said here. "We have therefore asked the French helicopter crews 
making these missions to refuse," these controls, she said. 
  "The French authorities note that UN Security Council 
Resolution 913 demands an immediate and definite lifting of all 
blockages on the free circulation of UNPROFOR," (the UN 
Protection Force) in Bosnia-Herzegovina, Colonna added. Flights 
by British and French UN helicopters between Gorazde and 
Sarajevo were delayed again Monday by the Serbs. 
  According to the office of the UN High Commissioner for 
Refugees (UNHCR) -- struggling to save the most seriously 
wounded people in Gorazde -- travelling times have been 
quadrupled by Serb controls. The delays were fatal for the most 
seriously wounded patients at Gorazde hospital, an aid worker 
said at Sarajevo. 
  Of the 600 due for emergency evacuation, 154 have been 
evacuated from Gorazde since Sunday. Sixty nine people were 
evacuated Monday up to the middle of the afternoon. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

