<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Visegrad, 25 Apr (TANJUG) -- The decision by Radovan 
Karadzic, the president of the Srpska republic, and Yasushi 
Akashi, the UN secretary-general's special envoy, on the 
withdrawal of the Serb forces around Gorazde is being 
successfully implemented, Milan Gvero, deputy commander of the 
Srpska republic's army, told a TANJUG reporter today. 
  According to Gvero, the Serb soldiers have withdrawn three 
km 
from the center of Gorazde, and the decision on the evacuation 
of the wounded and civilians from Gorazde has also been 
implemented. The passage of humanitarian convoys to Gorazde is 
also continuing successfully, Gvero added. 
  He particularly stressed that he expected that UNPROFOR [UN 
Protection Forces] deployed along the separation lines would not 
allow any further provocative actions by the Muslims from 
Gorazde. 
  Gvero also said that today he had demanded from UN officials 
that all Serb prisoners be unconditionally released from Gorazde 
and that this should not be considered a prisoner exchange. 
For, according to General Gvero, the Serbs have shown goodwill 
so many times, by allowing humanitarian convoys in and by 
withdrawing their troops from Gorazde. 
  It is time that the other side shows goodwill too, Gen. 
Gvero 
stressed. 

</TEXT>

