<F P=103> LD2504205094 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" item] </F>
  [Text] Doboj, April 25 (TANJUG) -- Bosnian Moslem forces on 
Monday stepped up the intensity of their attacks on Bosnian Serb 
positions and villages in the wider region of Doboj in northern 
Bosnia. 
  Moslems attacked Serb defence positions west of Doboj with 
strong small arms and mortar fire and tried to carry out an 
infantry attack, but it was repulsed, Bosnian Serb military 
sources said. 
  Moslem forces carried out a strong infantry attack northeast 
of Teslic (southwest of Doboj), planning to break through the 
Serb defence lines, but Bosnian Serb units repulsed this attack 
and forced the Moslem formations to retreat. 
  Moslems on Monday also stepped up attacks from anti-aircraft 
weapons and small arms northeast of Doboj, but the attacks 
ceased after the Serb side returned strong fire. 

</TEXT>

