<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Exchanges Prisoners With Abdic's Forces </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Exchanges Prisoners With Abdic's Forces </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2504193094 Paris AFP in English 1911 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2504193094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Zagreb, April 25 (AFP) -- The Bosnian Government and 
secessionists freed 356 Moslem prisoners of war in the Bihac 
pocket in northern Bosnia, the International Committee of the 
Red Cross (ICRC) said here Monday [25 April]. 
  Moslem secessionist forces led by Fikret Abdic, controlling 
the north of the pocket, freed 280 prisoners, and troops loyal 
to Bosnian President Alija Izetbegovic in the south freed 76, 
the ICRC said. The exchanges followed the signing of an 
agreement between the two sides April 23. 
  ICRC representatives held discussions with each prisoner to 
make sure they were happy crossing the front line to rejoin 
their own side. The forces have clashed intermittently since 
Abdic declared autonomy late last year for Bihac. 

</TEXT>

