<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-9412 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu080_p_94007" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-080 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  24 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage on New Freedom Union Party </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage on New Freedom Union Party </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    National Council Members Elected </H4>

<F P=102> LD2404115794 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1101 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2404115794 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 24 Apr--Hanna Suchocka, on the Democratic 
Union [UD] ticket, and Janusz Lewandowski, from the Liberal 
Democratic Congress [KLD], have received the largest numbers of 
votes in the elections to the National Council of the Freedom 
Union [UW]. Such results were announced on Sunday at the first 
UW National Congress. 
  Tadeusz Mazowiecki, the leader of the party, and Donald 
Tusk, 
deputy chairman, enter the Council automatically. 
  Among the Council's members who have a UD pedigree, Jacek 
Taylor came second and Andrzej Potocki third. On the liberals' 
list were Michal Boni and Jan Krzysztof Bielecki, respectively. 

</TEXT>

