<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage on New Freedom Union Party </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage on New Freedom Union Party </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Policy Outlined at News Conference </H4>

<F P=102> LD2404142794 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1311 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2404142794 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 24 Apr--The merger of the Democratic Union 
and the Liberal Democratic Congress was the only logical 
solution for our parties, Tadeusz Mazowiecki, chairman of the 
Freedom Union [UW], said on Sunday at the first news conference 
held by the new party. 
  Commenting on the fact that Jacek Kuron refused to be a 
candidate for the leadership of the new party, Mazowiecki 
expressed his regret. "I know that the comments on this matter 
will be unfavorable. I tried to persuade him to put his 
candidacy forward, but he did not want to do it. However, this 
fact does not change our respect for Jacek Kuron," he emphasized. 
  When asked whom the Freedom Union would support in the 
presidential elections, he said that the UW would definitely not 
support a candidate of the Democratic Left Alliance or the 
Polish Peasant Party, and that the attitude of the UW towards 
the present president was critical. He stressed that, for the 
time being, his party would not comment on the matter "in order 
not to attract any blows. However, the time will come when we 
shall make a statement." 
  It is not yet known what the logo of the new party will be. 
It has only been established that it will be blue. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

