<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage on New Freedom Union Party </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage on New Freedom Union Party </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Says Rebirth Process `Under Threat' </H4>

<F P=102> LD2404122294 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1107 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2404122294 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 24 Apr--The congress of the Freedom Union 
adopted a resolution today that says the process of rebirth of 
the state and its economy, initiated in 1989, is under threat. 
The congress obliged the party authorities to prepare a strategy 
for "the second step along the road of reforms in Poland." 
  The national congress found essential the earliest possible 
setting up of specialized secretariats to analyze the situation 
in particular spheres of social and economic life. "Their joint 
task would be to formulate the strategy of the second step along 
the road of reforms in Poland and winning its allies' and social 
partners' support for it," the resolution reads. 
  People heading these secretariats would constitute a sort of 
"shadow cabinet." 

</TEXT>

