<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Deputy Defense Minister Resigns </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deputy Defense Minister Resigns </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2504135094 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1300 
GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2504135094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] After submitting his resignation, Deputy Minister of 
Defense Boyko Noev stated that recently intensified political 
pressure prevents him from implementing his duties. He hoped 
that the government, I quote, is able to overcome the difficult 
situation. [no reference to close of quotation as heard] 
  On the other hand, according to a report from the Council of 
Ministers, [Defense] Minister Aleksandrov heard about his 
deputy's resignation from journalists. 

</TEXT>

