<F P=101> Albania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Embargo `Seriously' Damaging Mining Industry </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Embargo `Seriously' Damaging Mining Industry </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2304165794 Tirana ATA in English 1008 GMT 23 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2304165794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Albania Continues To Suffer Economic Damage Due to the </F>
Embargo on Former Yugoslavia" -- ATA headline] 
  [Text] Tirana, April 23 (ATA) -- Albanian Government's 
observation of the embargo on former Yugoslavia has seriously 
damaged the mineral industry in the northeastern zone of 
Albania. The mine of Kam, Tropoje district, is mostly suffering 
the consequences of the embargo. Its productive activity is 
almost suspended. 
  Earlier, the mine exported chrome ore for the enriching 
factory of "Deva" of Gjakove in Kosova. Due to the application 
of the embargo for 1992-1993 alone, about 60,000 tons of mineral 
were not exported causing an economic damage of about 2.7 
million dollars. Three productive sectors have been closed and 
about 250 workers are on assistance. Annual production has 
dropped about 17,000 tons from 60,000 tons it was earlier. So 
far, the respective structures of the United Nations 
Organisation have not done anything to compensate the damage 
caused by the implementation of the embargo on former Yugoslavia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

