<H3> <TI>   Ministry Holds `Incontestable' Proof on Detainees </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry Holds `Incontestable' Proof on Detainees </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2304153594 Tirana ATA in English 1019 GMT 23 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2304153594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, April 23 (ATA) -- "The recent detention by 
the Ministry of Public Order are not and has not been done on 
basis of nationality but according to their citizenship," the 
spokesman of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs said yesterday, 
commenting on the detention for keeping arms without permission, 
drugs and criminal anticonstitutional activity. 
  The spokesman said that the Ministry of Public Order 
possesses incontestable proofs and will make them available for 
any international investigating commission interested in them. 
"Each Albanian citizen is equal before the law and the 
intervention of any state for protecting them is unacceptable. 
Such acts violate the sovereignty of the Albanian state," the 
spokesman concludes. 
  Some 11 persons have been detained for keeping arms without 
permission and many criminal anti-constitutional documentations 
during a control made recently by the Ministry of Public Order. 
The documentations proves the Greek expansionist intentions 
against Albania and the Greek flagrant endeavour to Hellenize 
the Albania's southern territories. 

</TEXT>

