<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Albania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Elimination of Place-Names in Montenegro Noted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Elimination of Place-Names in Montenegro Noted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2404155294 Tirana ATA in English 0812 GMT 24 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2404155294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, April 24 (ATA) -- The Constitution of the 
Republic of Montenegro recognizes the right of the use of the 
two languages, but this right has been not applied for the 
Albanians. The inscriptions and names of places in the Albanian 
language are disappearing with each passing day. Albanian 
toponymy is in the objective of destruction and with thus 
eliminating the traces of civilization and the presence of the 
Albanians as well. Wherever you are in Ulqin, you could hardly 
understand where you are. Everywhere you can read ULCINJ, 
according to a report in RILINDJA. The Albanian names of the 
places have been changed in order to eliminate the Albanian 
identity of the toponymy. Changes of the pure Albanian names 
have been also made in the official administration and they are 
now being applied in the schools and even in the diplomas of the 
Albanian students who have attended classes in Albanian schools. 

</TEXT>

