BFN 

  [Excerpts] Sofia, April 25 (BTA) -- The Council of 
Ministers today relieved of his post Todor Borilkov, a member of 
the Privatization Agency's Supervisory Board who had tendered 
his resignation. [passage omitted] 
  Behind closed doors the cabinet today approved a project for 
the construction of the Bulgarian section of a railway linking 
Bulgaria and Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of 
Macedonia -- FYROM] in the area of Guesevo and Kumanovo. The 
existing railway service is through Serbia. The cabinet 
approved a draft agreement that will serve as a basis for 
further talks with Macedonia on the construction of the railway, 
the government spokesman told the press. 

