<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Hungary </F>
<H3> <TI>   SZDZS News Conference on Election Plans </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SZDZS News Conference on Election Plans </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2504101594 Budapest MTI in English 1708 GMT 24 Apr 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2504101594 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 24 April (MTI) -- The Alliance of Free 
Democrats [SZDSZ] is to decide about participation in a 
government coalition at a delegates assembly following the 
parliamentary elections in May. Until then, it will concentrate 
on achieving a good result at the elections. 
  This earlier decision was confirmed on Sunday [24 April] in 
Budapest, during a meeting by the party's National Council. 
  SZDSZ campaign chief Balint Magyar reported about the 
meeting 
at a press conference. He said that if the SZDSZ achieves a good 
result at the elections, that will imply a guarantee for 
replacing the current government coalition, and for forming a 
new government. Magyar also said that the chances of the SZDSZ 
are now better than ever before, and the party will most 
certainly be a political factor to be reckoned with when forming 
the new government. 
  SZDSZ prime minister candidate Gabor Kuncze briefed 
journalists about his participation in the founding session of 
the Democratic Union of Slovakia, in Bratisla on Saturday [23 
April], and his talks with Slovak Prime Minister Jozef Moravcik, 
who was elected chairman of the union. 
  Kuncze said the good will exists in Slovakia to settle 
bilateral relations and uphold the dialogue. 

</TEXT>

