<H3> <TI>   Strikers Urge Pawlak To Overrule Pol </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Strikers Urge Pawlak To Overrule Pol </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2504091394 Warsaw PAP in English 0858 GMT 25 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD2504091394 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kalisz, April 25 -- The All-Poland Strike Committee 
of the brown coal mines addressed a letter to the prime minister 
expressing the hope that the stand of the industry minister 
Marek Pol did not represent the position of the government, 
press spokesman of Solidarity's strike committee at the "Konin" 
mine Zdzislaw Stasiak announced on Monday. 
  We are expecting the prime minister to immediately lift the 
decision concerning the restructuring of the brown coal mining 
industry, Stasiak said. According to him, the responsibility 
for the further development of the situation now rests entirely 
on Prime Minister Waldemar Pawlak. Stasiak added that since the 
industry minister's messages fail to propose any new solutions 
and only increase tension among the strikers "There is no need 
to further exchange correspondence with him". 

</TEXT>

