<H3> <TI>   Miners To Continue Strike </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Miners To Continue Strike </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2504162594 Warsaw PAP in English 1419 GMT 25 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD2504162594 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Belchatow, April 25 -- "Even if the government 
withdraws or annuls the decision concerning transformations in 
brown coal mining and establishment of three holdings, the 
Solidarity strike committee of the brown coal mines will not end 
the strike but will only suspend it," Jozef Polkowski, a member 
of the strike committee, told a press conference at the 
Belchatow mine on Monday [25 April]. 
  This would mean an increase of coal deliveries to power 
plants which now receive only strategic amounts of fuel 
necessary to keep them going. 
  Polkowski added that after the decision has been either 
suspended or annulled, the strike committee might start 
negotiations concerning nation-wide demands of the trade union. 

</TEXT>

