<H3> <TI>   Hard Coal Mines To Strike 25 Apr </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hard Coal Mines To Strike 25 Apr </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2504165894 Warsaw PAP in English 1452 GMT 25 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD2504165894 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Katowice, April 25 -- Chairmen of Solidarity hard 
coal workplace committees decided here on Monday [25 April] to 
start a "rotary and indefinite-time" strike in hard coal mines 
on Monday night, head of the Solidarity black coal section Karol 
Luzniak said on Monday. 
  Luzniak stressed the strike would be legal as Solidarity has 
entered into a collective dispute with the government. 
  Meanwhile, 50 Solidarity factory committees confirmed their 
participation in a two-hour warning strike, to be held in 
Poland's central-eastern region on Tuesday, secretary of the 
region board in Lublin Waldemar Dudziak said in Lublin on Monday. 

</TEXT>

