BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, April 25 -- Andrzej Dobroczek of the 
National Power Distribution Office said on Monday [25 April] 
that a planned strike by hard coal miners would not disturb the 
production of electricity, at least for some time. Dobroczek 
said that production of electricity could be continued as power 
plants have stocked enough hard coal. 

</TEXT>

