<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Piotrkow Trybunalski, April 26 -- The All-Poland 
Strike Committee of the brown coal mines agreed on Tuesday [26 
April] to deliver coal in quantities sufficient to generate some 
25 percent of the energy generated by individual power plants. 
The decision was announced following industry minister's 
declaration during talks with union leaders here that he is 
cancelling orders concerning the restructuring of the brown coal 
sector. 
  Spokesman for Solidarity's national commission said that the 
decision on resumption of coal deliveries will be lifted at 2000 
hrs on Thursday if the government side fails to adopt a 
time-table, approved by Solidarity, of dealing with the demands 
put forward by the union. 

