<H3> <TI>   Moravcik Not To Accept Conference Invitation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moravcik Not To Accept Conference Invitation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2604083894 Prague CTK in English 1755 GMT 25 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2604083894 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, April 25 (CTK) -- Slovak Premier Jozef 
Moravcik will probably not take part in an international 
conference on liberalism in Central and East Europe, being 
organized by the Friedrich Naumann Foundation this Saturday in 
the Hungarian town of Visegrad, Gergely Prolle from the 
foundation told CTK today. 
  Moravcik has been invited to attend the conference both by 
the foundation and leading representatives of two Hungarian 
liberal parties -- the Union of Free Democrats and the Union of 
Young Democrats. 
  Prolle said that Moravcik had excused himself, citing the 
lack of time, already last Friday. On the other hand in an 
interview with representatives of Hungarian liberal parties in 
Bratislava Moravcik has allegedly made it clear that he would 
attend the Visegrad meeting of Central European liberal 
politicians if possible. 
  Liberal politicians and representatives of liberal parties 
from all Central European countries and some Western politicians 
are to take part in the conference. It is expected that 
Chairman of the Liberal International Otto Lambsdorff will also 
take part. Representatives of some liberal parties from the 
Czech Republic have also been invited, organizers said. 

</TEXT>

