<H3> <TI>   Moravcik's Popularity Rating Improving </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moravcik's Popularity Rating Improving </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2204170094 Prague CTK in English 1426 GMT 22 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2204170094 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava April 22 (CTK) -- Former Premier 
Vladimir Meciar is still the most popular politician in Slovakia 
with 26 percent of favour among would-be voters, a poll 
conducted by the Slovak Statistical Office in early March 
revealed. 
  He is followed by President Michal Kovac and current Premier 
Jozef Moravcik (25 percent each). Moravcik's rating improved 20 
percent over the last two weeks, the poll showed. 
  Then follow: Peter Weiss, Chairman of the Democratic Left 
(SDL) with 13 percent, Parliament Chairman Ivan Gasparovic with 
10 percent and Deputy Premier Roman Kovac with seven percent. 
  No politician is trusted by 25 percent of those polled, 
which 
is a marked decline in comparison with February when the figure 
was 41 percent. 

</TEXT>

