<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Slovakia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poll Reveals Split Over Meciar's Dismissal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Poll Reveals Split Over Meciar's Dismissal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2504120694 Prague CTK in English 1028 GMT 25 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2504120694 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava April 25 (CTK) -- Some 44 percent of 
Slovaks agree with Vladimir Meciar's dismissal from the 
premiership, while 39 percent do not, a poll conducted by the 
Slovak Statistical Office in early April revealed. 
  Some 17 percent are indifferent to the issue, the poll 
showed. 
  Meciar's fall (on March 11) was welcomed by ethnic 
Hungarians 
(80 percent), entrepreneurs (55 percent) and followers of the 
"dissidents" from Meciar's Movement for a Democratic Slovakia 
(88 percent). 

</TEXT>

