<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Albanian President Visits, Signs Agreements </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Albanian President Visits, Signs Agreements </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2704172294 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1600 
GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2704172294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Two agreements were signed during the first day of 
the official visit of Albanian President Sali Berisha to 
Bulgaria. The first was an agreement on trade and economic 
cooperation and the second was an agreement on the mutual 
protection of investments. The agreements were signed by Selim 
Pelurtaja, Albanian minister of economy and trade, and Bulgarian 
Trade Minister Valentin Karabashev. 
  In brief statements after the official ceremony to sign the 
agreements, Bulgarian President Zhelyu Zhelev and Albanian 
President Sali Berisha expressed their satisfaction with the 
development of relations between the two countries. They pointed 
out that this tendency was confirmed by the two documents, which 
regulate bilateral cooperation between Bulgaria and Albania. 
  Presidents Zhelev and Berisha had a 45-minute face-to-face 
talk, but refused any statements before the joint news 
conference scheduled to take place on 29 April. 

</TEXT>

