<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Democratic Union of Slovakia Formed in Merger </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Democratic Union of Slovakia Formed in Merger </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2304194794 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1500 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2304194794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1500 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Alliance of Democrats of the Slovak Republic and 
the Alternative of Political Realism have merged into a new 
political body called the Democratic Union of Slovakia 
[Demokraticka Unia Slovenska--DEUS] at a meeting this morning in 
the Charlie Center in Bratislava. Anna Samelova and Ivan Samel 
are on the line to report more in detail about the assembly: 
  [Samel] [passage omitted] This morning the delegates 
acquainted themselves with reports about the assemblies of the 
Alliance and the Alternative, and with statements expressing 
their willingness to merge. They discussed and approved the 
statutes of the new party. Following a lengthy discussion in 
the afternoon, they also approved the DEUS's program. 
  [Samelova] This afternoon, the assembly delegates elected 
senior DEUS officials. The result of the vote is as follows: 
Jozef Moravcik is the chairman, Milan Knazko is the first deputy 
chairman, Viliam Vaskovic is the deputy chairman for economy, 
and Roman Kovac is the deputy chairman for social affairs and 
culture. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

