<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   TA SR Director General Dismisses Chief Editor </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    TA SR Director General Dismisses Chief Editor </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2804092294 Bratislava REPUBLIKA in Slovak 21 Apr 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU2804092294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava REPUBLIKA </F>
<F P=105>  Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by "(R)": "And the Purge Continues..."] </F>
  [Text] Immediately after he was introduced to his post by 
Deputy Prime Minister Roman Kovac, newly appointed TA SR 
Director General Ivan Melichercik recalled TA SR Chief Editor 
Dusan Kerny and Economic Deputy Rudolf Wurm. Kerny, the first 
chief editor of an independent Slovak news agency, was recalled 
40 minutes after Deputy Prime Minister Roman Kovac, who praised 
TA SR's reportage and said that it was "done well, to a high 
professional standard," had left the agency's offices. Kerny 
managed the editorial office during the transition period 
following independence from the CTK service and organized the 
first direct subscription to foreign news agencies, including 
REUTER, AFP, DPA, and others. He also organized the first 
Slovak service in English for foreign consumers and established 
the first international editorial office in Slovakia since 1948. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

