<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Dukovany Plant Considered `Safe and Reliable' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Dukovany Plant Considered `Safe and Reliable' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2604161794 Prague MLADA FRONTA DNES in Czech 25 Apr 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> AU2604161794 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague MLADA FRONTA DNES </F>
<F P=105>  Czech </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by "(dz)": "There Were More Than 300 Cases of </F>
Malfunction at Dukovany in 1993"] 
  [Text] Dukovany--At the Dukovany nuclear plant, in the 
vicinity of which environmentalists commemorated the eighth 
anniversary of the Chernobyl disaster, there were 315 cases of 
malfunction and deviations from the standard. 
  Three of them were described as failures due to flaws in 
security measures. The report that the State Office for Nuclear 
Safety drafted for the government states that the emergency 
signaling systems were activated 12 times in 1993. Despite this, 
the State Office for Nuclear Safety considers the operation of 
the Dukovany nuclear plant to be safe and reliable. 

</TEXT>

