<H3> <TI>   1993 Closing Balance Statement Accepted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    1993 Closing Balance Statement Accepted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2504171994 Prague HOSPODARSKE NOVINY in Czech 21 Apr 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> AU2504171994 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague HOSPODARSKE NOVINY </F>
<F P=105>  Czech </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by "dz": "The Government Approved 1993 Budget </F>
Closing Statement"] 
  [Text] Prague--In its session yesterday, the government 
approved the draft 1993 government budget closing statement. 
The statement shows a surplus of 1.1 billion korunas. 
According to Deputy Prime Minister Josef Lux, 200 million of 
this surplus is to be used for the region program, 87 million 
for additional payments on the Bilina mine credit, 339 million 
for the internal revenue computer system, and 454 million to 
increase reserves for dealing with social problems. The 
government described last year as successful. "It was the first 
time that a growth of labor productivity could be registered--by 
3.1 percent--and the foreign currency reserves reached their 
maximum in the history of our state--$6 billion," Lux 
emphasized. The government acknowledged the Czech National Bank 
report on the balance of payments and monetary development for 
1993. "The debt of the Czech Republic increased by $1.8 billion 
to $8.7 billion, 76 percent of which are long-term obligations. 
Overall, we are creditors, but a great part of our claims is 
difficult to collect," Lux commented. 

</TEXT>

