<H4>    Solidarity Calls For General Strike </H4>

<F P=102> LD2604195594 Warsaw Third Program Radio Network in Polish 
1900 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2604195594 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Third Program Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] [Announcer] Let's try again to get through by phone 
to our reporter Ernest Zorzun in Belchatow: 
  [Zorzun] I am speaking from Belchatow, bringing the latest 
news. Solidarity has called a nationwide general strike for 28 
April. The national protest action staff have stated that this 
action is being taken after today's talks with the industry 
minister and the fruitless wait for the government to implement 
the trade union's demands. The action will be continuous strike 
action and is aimed at putting pressure on the government in 
order to force it to quickly present a timetable for 
implementing the demands of the national trade unions. Minister 
Pol was urged (?to do this) during this morning's talks, Marian 
Krzaklewski stated. We have no other way, Krzaklewski added, at 
the end of a hastily organized news conference. 
  [Announcer] Thank you. I remind you that the government is 
meeting just now to discuss the strike situation. 

</TEXT>

