<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on Nationwide Strike </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reportage on Nationwide Strike </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Non-Solidarity Unions Suspend Strike </H4>

<F P=102> LD2704141094 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1059 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2704141094 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 27 Apr--In a letter on 27 April to Prime 
Minister Waldemar Pawlak and Industry Minister Marek Pol, the 
Trade Union Federation of Brown Coal Mining said that its 
members are suspending their participation in the strike and are 
ready for negotiations with the government on demands put 
forward by the union. 
  "Because Decision No. 30 has been annulled, the federation 
strike committee is suspending its participation in the strike 
and obliging enterprise commissions to withdraw from strike 
committees in enterprises after internal demands are met. When 
the strike has been suspended, we are open to negotiations with 
the government on the union's demands", federation miners said. 

</TEXT>

