<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN Suspends All Humanitarian Aid Convoys </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN Suspends All Humanitarian Aid Convoys </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2604171494 Paris AFP in English 1702 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2604171494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Zagreb, April 26 (AFP) -- The United Nations 
suspended Tuesday all aid convoys inside Bosnia-Herzegovina, a 
spokesman said here. Manoel de Almeida, a spokesman for the UN 
High Commissioner for Refugees, said the convoys had been 
suspended on security grounds. Serb forces face a 0001 GMT 
deadline to pull their heavy weapons away from Gorazde or face 
NATO air strikes. All active convoys in the war-torn former 
Yugoslav republic returned to their bases by mid-afternoon 
Tuesday in line with the directive, which the spokesman 
described as a "completely normal procedure." 
  De Almeida said an aid convoy which left Belgrade Tuesday 
morning for the battered eastern Bosnian enclave of Goradze -- 
the third to set out for the town -- returned to the Serbian 
capital later in the day after being blocked by Serbian forces 
at the border. An earlier convoy from Belgrade which had been 
blocked by Serb forces arrived Tuesday morning in Gorazde, said 
the UNHCR's spokesman in Serbia, Lyndall Sachs. The first 
convoy to reach Gorazde after Bosnian Serb forces eased a 
three-week siege of the town arrived there Sunday. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

