<H3> <TI>   Army Breaks Through Serbian Lines Near Travnik </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Breaks Through Serbian Lines Near Travnik </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2804124394 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1200 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2804124394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [7th Corps Information Service report] </F>
  [Text] After the days-long futile attempts of Karadzic's 
army to capture our defense lines on the Vlasic plateau, a part 
of the Bosnia-Herzegovina 7th Corps elite units, in a strong 
counteroffensive, this morning managed to break through the 
Chetnik lines and capture the wider area of Mt. Neokrnje located 
in the triangle between the Travnik, Teslic, and Skender Vakuf 
communes. 
  Our defenders' action has significantly expanded the free 
territory on the Vlasic plateau. Dozens of Chetniks have been 
killed and we have captured a nice collection of material and 
technical equipment [words indistinct] -- a 105-mm howitzer, a 
Praga antiaircraft weapon, a SAM-110 vehicle, 120-mm mortar, a 
antiaircraft machine gun mounted on a tractor, (?several pieces) 
of small caliber weaponry, and a substantial quantity of 
ammunition and military equipment. As we file this report, the 
members of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army 7th Corps have captured 
the mountain resort on Mt. Neokrnje which the Chetniks used as 
quarters for manpower and hardware during battles. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>
